name: dfs.qjournal.write-txns.timeout.ms
description:
Write timeout in milliseconds when writing to a quorum of remote
    journals.

name: dfs.client.slow.io.warning.threshold.ms
description:
The threshold in milliseconds at which we will log a slow
    io warning in a dfsclient. By default, this parameter is set to 30000
    milliseconds (30 seconds).

name: dfs.namenode.file.close.num-committed-allowed
description:
Normally a file can only be closed with all its blocks are committed.
    When this value is set to a positive integer N, a file can be closed
    when N blocks are committed and the rest complete.

name: mapreduce.jobhistory.datestring.cache.size
description:
Size of the date string cache. Effects the number of directories
  which will be scanned to find a job.

name: mapreduce.reduce.shuffle.fetch.retry.interval-ms
description:
Time of interval that fetcher retry to fetch again when some
  non-fatal failure happens because of some events like NM restart.

name: dfs.namenode.fs-limits.max-xattr-size
description:
The maximum combined size of the name and value of an extended attribute
    in bytes. It should be larger than 0, and less than or equal to maximum
    size hard limit which is 32768.
    Support multiple size unit suffix(case insensitive), as described in
    dfs.blocksize.
